<HEADLINE> No criminal charges in New Jersey boating accident  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   OCEAN CITY, N.J. (AP) - No criminal charges will be filed
against a Pennsylvania man whose cabin cruiser collided into a
speedboat near Ocean City, killing four people last month, New
Jersey State Police said Monday.
</P>
<P>
   The operator of the speedboat, Dominnick Laspata, 26, of
Westville, N.J., and his three passengers were killed when the boat
was struck by a cabin cruiser piloted by John Lego, 52, of
Lansdale, Pa.
</P>
<P>
   Lego was issued waterway violations, which are similar to
traffic violations, for running his 30-foot Pro Line cabin cruiser
into the 26-foot Sonic speedboat operated by Laspata.
</P>
<P>
   Five of the nine people on board Lego's boat suffered minor
injuries.
</P>
</TEXT>
