<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 31 horses dead in barn fire  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   NORTH SALEM, N.Y. (AP) - Fire raced through a barn at a horse
farm in northern Westchester, killing 31 horses, many of them
mounts for children learning to ride.
</P>
<P>
   The blaze at Breakaway Farms on Route 121 in North Salem broke
out at about 5:15 a.m. Monday, and the wooden structure was
engulfed by the time firefighters arrived, said Chief Neil Caputo,
of the Croton Falls Fire Department. The cause was unknown.
</P>
<P>
   The barn was reduced to an ashen outline, the dead horses buried
by barn workers and firefighters.
</P>
<P>
   A neighbor, Laura Schwartz, told News 12 Westchester that she
saw ''a wall of flame'' shooting up from the barn when she awoke.
</P>
<P>
   Katherine Grayson, whose daughter had a horse at the barn, said
of the animal, ''He was her life.''
</P>
<P>
   ''For her, it's like losing a child,'' she said.
</P>
<P>
   Another neighbor, Debbie Kilcullen, said Breakaway Farms was
''kid-oriented,'' with horse shows and a summer camp.
</P>
<P>
   Last month, a fire at a Brooklyn stable killed 21 horses.
</P>
</TEXT>
