<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-11 00:27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> New Jersey teen accused of sexually assaulting camper  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   GREENFIELD, N.H. (AP) - After an 18-hour manhunt, police Monday
arrested a camp counselor accused of sexually assaulting a
13-year-old boy.
</P>
<P>
   Police say Juan Diaz, 19, of Clifton, N.J., fled into the woods
near Brantwood Camp on Sunday afternoon. He was found late Monday
morning and arrested on charges of felonious sexual assault.
</P>
<P>
   Diaz was being held at the Valley Street Jail in Manchester on
$100,000 bail.
</P>
<P>
   Brantwood is an overnight summer camp, police said.
</P>
<P>
   Camp director Amy Willey released a statement early Tuesday
morning saying Diaz was a temporary, first-time counselor who has
been fired. Police are still investigating, but the incident
appeared to be isolated, she said.
</P>
<P>
   ''We must emphasize that no child is presently in danger or at
risk at Brantwood, and we will continue with our mission to provide
a quality summer camp experience to young boys and girls,'' the
statement said.
</P>
<P>
   The camp reported Diaz to police, it said.
</P>
<P>
   Willey would not comment further or say how many children attend
the camp.
</P>
</TEXT>
