<HEADLINE> 10 Said Dead in Indonesia Bus Crash  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   JAKARTA, Indonesia (AP) -- A bus plunged into a deep ravine on
Indonesia's main island of Java, killing 10 people and injuring 13
others in a group on its way to a wedding, reports said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
   The vehicle was overloaded with 39 passengers when its brakes
failed and it skidded off the road and into the valley near
Sarangan village Sunday, the official Antara news agency said.
Sarangan is about 420 miles east of Jakarta.
</P>
<P>
   Most passengers escaped death as the bus got stuck in the
branches of a pine tree instead of crashing to the valley bottom,
the report said.
</P>
<P>
   Many Indonesian bus companies have tried to maximize profits by
cutting back on maintenance and packing vehicles with passengers.
Indonesia's roads have also deteriorated in recent years. Both
factors have led to a string of deadly accidents in recent months.
</P>
