<HEADLINE> Dow Up 5; Nasdaq Down 3  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- Stock prices have opened narrowly mixed, with
the Dow Jones Industrial Average up 5 points in today's early
going. Advancers and decliners are evenly split on the New York
Stock Exchange.
</P>
<P>
   The Nasdaq Composite Index is off 3 points and the Standard and
Poor's 500 Stock Index is down fractionally.
</P>
<P>
   Wall Street doesn't like unknowns, and there are plenty of them
for investors right now.
</P>
<P>
   Of immediate concern -- a speech Fed chairman Alan Greenspan is
giving this morning, and another one he's giving tomorrow.
</P>
<P>
   And, more lasting, the second-quarter profit reporting period is
about to get under way in earnest.
</P>
<P>
   Yahoo! is scheduled to release its quarterly results after
today's closing bell.
</P>
<P>
   Analysts say all that uncertainty could well leave the market
with some modest losses today.
</P>
<P>
   Overseas, the popular averages are mostly lower in Europe.
</P>
</TEXT>
