<HEADLINE> Two Killed in Navy Plane Crash  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   LEXINGTON PARK, Md. (AP) -- A Navy jet crashed Tuesday during a
training exercise at Patuxent River Naval Air Station, killing both
people aboard.
</P>
<P>
   The twin-engine T-38A Talon jet trainer crashed about 9:40 a.m.
while it was approaching a runway, according to a news release from
the base in southern Maryland, southeast of Washington. Base
spokesman John Romer said the crash site was on base property but
he didn't know how far away it was from a runway.
</P>
<P>
   Air station firefighters and rescue workers were on the scene
almost immediately.
</P>
<P>
   Base officials were withholding the crew members' names until
their next of kin were notified. The crash was being investigated.
</P>
<P>
   The two-seat jet was made by Northrop between 1961 and 1972.
</P>
