<HEADLINE> French Actor Undergoes Bypass  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   PARIS (AP) -- French movie star Gerard Depardieu underwent
successful coronary bypass surgery and is recovering in a Paris
hospital, his film agency said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
   ArtMedia said the 51-year-old actor had surgery Monday at the
Foch hospital in Suresnes, outside Paris. The agency said doctors
decided to perform the operation following tests, but that there
was no emergency. It said Depardieu was expected to recover fully.
</P>
<P>
   Doctor Gilles Dreyfus, who conducted the six-hour operation,
said the actor was admitted last week after suffering from chest
pains.
</P>
<P>
   ''There was no alternative treatment,'' Dreyfus said, adding
that the patient was doing very well but would have to stay in
hospital another eight or nine days.
</P>
<P>
   Depardieu is France's most prolific actor, with more than 100
movies to his credit, including ''Cyrano de Bergerac,'' ''The
Return of Martin Guerre'' and the English-language comedy ''Green
Card.''
</P>
<P>
   In May, he attended the Cannes Film Festival in southern France
to promote the lavish period drama ''Vatel'' and was filming a
comedy when he fell ill. He is expected to return to the set soon,
his film agency said.
</P>
