<HEADLINE> French Clinic Closed Temporarily  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   PARIS (AP) -- French health authorities shut down a clinic
outside Paris on Tuesday after former employees claimed as many as
40 elderly or seriously ill patients were killed with overdoses of
sedatives.
</P>
<P>
   A state prosecutor ordered the closure of the La Martiniere
clinic for an inquiry into allegations of homicide, euthanasia and
theft, judicial officials said.
</P>
<P>
   They said police suspect that between 25 and 40 patients were
killed with a powerful cocktail of sedatives administered by clinic
personnel.
</P>
<P>
   On Sunday, the state prosecutor, Laurent Davenas, told France
Inter radio that police seized medical files from the clinic after
receiving what he called ''troubling testimonies'' from employees
and former employees.
</P>
<P>
   In a statement Tuesday, the regional hospital association
announced the closure of the clinic, located in Saclay, south of
Paris and said its 120 patients would be transferred to other
health centers in the area.
</P>
