<HEADLINE> Ex-husband charged with running over former spouse  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   ARCADE, N.Y.(AP) - Police charged a man with second-degree
attempted murder for allegedly running over his ex-wife and one of
her co-workers.
</P>
<P>
   Bouakham Onsa, 37, was in serious condition at Erie County
Medical Center Tuesday. Police said she was in the parking lot on
her way to work at Prestolite on Monday when the automobile attack
occurred.
</P>
<P>
   Akkhi Phiansouri, 51, after working his shift at Prestolite, ran
over her once, then backed up and hit her again as she attempted to
enter the building, said Arcade Police Chief John Laird.
</P>
<P>
   Terry Law, a co-worker, ran to warn Onsa the car was returning a
third time when they were both hit. The car was stopped by the
stairs of the building and Phiansouri tried to flee on foot, Laird
said, but other workers caught and held him until police arrived.
</P>
<P>
   Law, 46, of Freedom, was treated for facial injuries and
released, police said.
</P>
<P>
   Phiansouri is in Wyoming County Jail. No bail has been set.
</P>
<P>
   The attack was one of a series of violent incidents this year in
Wyoming County, including two homicides.
</P>
</TEXT>
