<HEADLINE> Police hunt for assailant of men in Brooklyn park  </HEADLINE>
By DONNA DE LA CRUZ
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) - Police are searching for a man wearing ''ninja''
type clothing who has sneaked up on four men in the past two weeks
in Brooklyn's Prospect Park, slashed three of them and clubbed one
in the leg.
</P>
<P>
   The attacks occurred in an area of the park known as the ''Vale
of Cashmere,'' frequented by gay men, which is why the NYPD's Hate
Crime Task Force is leading the investigation, Deputy Inspector
Barbara Sicilia said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
   ''It is probably the perception of the perpetrator that the
victims are all gay,'' said Sicilia, the task force's commander.
She declined to comment on the victims' sexual orientation.
</P>
<P>
   None of the victims got a good look at their attacker because he
strikes after midnight and was dressed all in black, and his face
was masked in black, Sicilia said.
</P>
<P>
   ''Some of the people have described it as like a ninja, all in
black, and with a mask,'' she said. ''And he has those kind of
moves - in one case - they see him slashing, with his hands, using
hand motions, as if he were cutting through the grass.''
</P>
<P>
   Police believe the suspect knows the park well, including the
heavily wooded area where the attacks have occurred.
</P>
<P>
   Sicilia added that the suspect is very quiet when he approaches
his victims.
</P>
<P>
   ''The perp comfortably walks up and you don't know anything is
going to happen and then all of a sudden - boom - you're getting
slashed or you're getting hit,'' she said.
</P>
<P>
   The first incident occurred shortly after midnight on June 28th.
A 33-year-old man was approached by a man who said ''I'm going to
kill you.'' The attacker then clubbed the victim in the leg with a
broom handle, Sicilia said.
</P>
<P>
   On July 4, shortly after 1 a.m., two men were walking together
when a third man approached. The two friends ran but one of them, a
47-year-old, was caught and slashed in the face, wrist, knee, ankle
and back with some type of cutting instrument, Sicilia said.
</P>
<P>
   The last two incidents both occurred on July 7th, within 30
minutes of each other. A 36-year-old man said he was walking on
Flatbush Avenue just outside the park around 2 a.m. when he was
approached and slashed on his face and nose.
</P>
<P>
   That victim called police and the next attack occurred despite a
police helicopter flying overhead, shining a light into the park.
</P>
<P>
   A 43-year-old man reported being slashed in the head, neck,
hands and arms.
</P>
<P>
   ''He (the suspect) has the audacity to attack the second guy''
while the helicopter is overhead, Sicilia said.
</P>
<P>
   Sicilia asked anyone with information to call Crime Stoppers at
800-577-TIPS. The city has offered a $10,000 reward for information
leading to the arrest and conviction of the suspect.
</P>
<P>
   ''This guy is so dangerous, we want to get him,'' Sicilia said.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
