<HEADLINE> Webster Agrees to Bucs' Contract  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   TAMPA, Fla. (AP) -- Third-round draft pick Nate Webster agreed to
a three-year contract with the Tampa Bay Buccaneers on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
   Webster, the 90th player taken in the draft, was a two-time
all-Big East selection at Miami. The 6-foot, 225-pound linebacker
made 301 tackles in three seasons with the Hurricanes.
</P>
<P>
   The Bucs have reached agreements with three of their five draft
picks. Fifth-round selection James Whalen, a tight end from
Kentucky, and sixth-rounder David Gibson, a safety from Southern
Cal, agreed to three-year deals Monday.
</P>
</TEXT>
