<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-11 18:42 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Twenty-year police veteran gets six months in rape of 16-year-old  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   RENSSELAER, N.Y. (AP) - A former Rensselaer police officer was
sentenced to six months in jail for raping and sodomizing a
16-year-old girl last year.
</P>
<P>
   Tuesday's sentencing with the victim in the courtroom is part of
a plea agreement Edward Farrell, 40, made in April. The crime
happened in January 1999 in Farrell's home.
</P>
<P>
   Farrell also faces five years probation and will have to
register with the state as a sex offender.
</P>
<P>
   The victim, now 17 years old, made a powerful statement at the
sentencing. She said her life was torn apart when her school
friends learned of the crime. She also warned Farell to never go
near her or her family.
</P>
<P>
   Farell, who claimed he had consensual sex with the girl, will
still get his police pension.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
