<HEADLINE> Woman arrested in Ocean County stabbing  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   TOMS RIVER, N.J. (AP) - A Lakewood woman was charged with
manslaughter in the stabbing death of her sister's boyfriend, Ocean
County prosecutors said.
</P>
<P>
   Tresa Pearson, 25, was arrested Tuesday afternoon. The stabbing
occurred shortly before 5:30 a.m., police said. Bail was set at
$50,000.
