<P>
   Police said the stabbing took place after Alvin Nicholson, 30,
of Howell, and his girlfriend, Tonya Pearson, got into a heated
verbal and physical argument in the foyer of a Lakewood apartment.
</P>
<P>
   Police didn't give Tonya Pearson's age or her hometown. It also
wasn't immediately clear who was living at the apartment.
</P>
<P>
   After the altercation, the sisters entered the apartment and
Nicholson tried to follow them, police said.
</P>
<P>
   Tresa Pearson then got a kitchen knife and used it to stab
Nicholson in the chest, prosecutors said.
</P>
<P>
   A medical examiner pronounced Nicholson dead at the scene.
</P>
<P>
   An autopsy was scheduled Tuesday evening to determine the cause
of death and the number of wounds.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
