<HEADLINE> Packers Acquire FB Powell  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   GREEN BAY, Wis. (AP) -- The Green Bay Packers acquired fullback
Marvin Powell from the New Orleans Saints on Tuesday in exchange
for tight end Lawrence Hart.
</P>
<P>
   Powell, who played at Southern California, appeared in nine
games for New Orleans last season, making two tackles on special
teams and rushing once.
</P>
<P>
   He is the son of 11-year NFL veteran Marvin Powell, the fourth
selection in the 1977 draft and an All-Pro offensive tackle who
played for the New York Jets and Tampa Bay Buccaneers.
</P>
<P>
   Hart, a 1998 graduate of Southern, spent much of last season on
the Packers' practice squad and all of 1998 on the Jets' practice
squad. He recently played for the Rhein Fire of NFL Europe, where
he started nine games and caught 18 passes.
</P>
<P>
   The Packers, who need to replace former starter Mark Chmura,
already have rookie Bubba Franks, Tyrone Davis and Kaseem Sinceno
vying for the job.
</P>
<P>
   Chmura was released after he was charged with enticing and
sexually assaulting a 17-year-old baby sitter at a post-prom party.
</P>
