<HEADLINE> Gutches, Burton To Wrestle for Spot  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   FARGO, N.D. (AP) -- Les Gutches, a 1996 Olympian, will wrestle
Charles Burton in a best-of-three series July 27 in Fargo, N.D.,
for a spot on the U.S. team at the Sydney Games.
</P>
<P>
   Gutches, the national freestyle champion at 187.25 pounds,
missed the Olympic trials last month because of injury.
</P>
<P>
   Gutches' back problems date to 1996, when he had surgery on a
ruptured disc. The injury didn't stop him from winning the world
championship in 1997, and five straight national titles. He said
the layoff should help him this time.
</P>
<P>
   ''To be honest, the longer it got delayed, the better,'' Gutches
said from Corvallis, Ore., where he was a standout at Oregon State.
''Having a month was great because I wanted the time to have
confidence in my health and training. Mentally, it's enough time to
get focused and ready for the match.''
</P>
<P>
   Gutches' last match was April 22, when he beat Burton at the
U.S. championships. He has defeated Burton the last four times they
have wrestled.
</P>
<P>
   ''I don't think either of us will surprise the other,'' Gutches
said. ''But even though there's not going to be any surprises, he's
still got good techniques. He still has enough ability that he
doesn't necessarily need to surprise anyone.''
</P>
</TEXT>
