<HEADLINE> Woman found dead in home fire  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   PLATTSBURGH, N.Y. (AP) - A woman was found dead in her home
after an early morning fire Monday.
</P>
<P>
   Police released few details, but said the fire and death
appeared suspicious, according to the Plattsburgh Press-Republican.
An autopsy is planned for Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
   Beverly Patzelt, 46, of the town of Plattsburgh was found dead
Monday.
</P>
<P>
   State Police Capt. Peter Person said Patzelts husband, Robert
Patzelt, reported that he awoke about 2 a.m. and found a fire
burning inside the house.
</P>
<P>
   He told police he tried to get his wife out of the home, but
could not, Person said. Patzelt then ran across the street to
another home to call 911.
</P>
<P>
   Person said that evidence inside the home where the body was
found raised some questions, but he would not elaborate on the
evidence or whether they have any suspects.
</P>
<P>
   Clinton County Coroner David Donah said the body was burned, but
there did not appear to be any other noticeable injuries.
</P>
<P>
   Patzelt, 51, was treated for minor injuries.
</P>
</TEXT>
