<HEADLINE> Investigators Re-Enact Erving Death  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   SANFORD, Fla. (AP) -- Divers trying to re-enact the death of Cory
Erving submerged his car Tuesday in the retention pond where his
body was found in the vehicle last week.
</P>
<P>
   In an effort to find out how the son of Julius Erving died,
divers went down with the black Volkswagen Passat in the pond near
their exclusive neighborhood, Orlando television station WKMG
reported.
</P>
<P>
   A spokesman for the Seminole County Sheriff's Office confirmed
that divers submerged the car, but wouldn't comment further.
</P>
<P>
   ''Crime scene investigators and a representative of the
(Florida) Highway Patrol are continuing the investigation,'' said
Sheriff's Lt. Ed Allen.
</P>
<P>
   Final preparations were made for Wednesday's memorial service,
expected to be attended by Bill Cosby, singer Patti LaBelle and
Larry Bird -- friends of Julius Erving, a member of the basketball
Hall of Fame.
</P>
<P>
   Eulogies were expected from the family's three remaining
children, three of Cory's friends and from Stedman Graham, a close
friend of the Ervings and Oprah Winfrey's longtime boyfriend.
</P>
<P>
   Cory, 19, was found dead in his car last Thursday, more than a
month after a search was launched to find him. He was last seen
alive on May 28 at a bakery where was buying bread for the family's
Memorial Day cookout.
</P>
<P>
   Sheriff Don Eslinger said the teen-ager's death was likely
accidental, although investigators haven't ruled anything out.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
