<HEADLINE> 49ers Expected To Name President  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   SAN FRANCISCO (AP) -- The San Francisco 49ers are expected to
hire a former toy company and video game executive as their
president and CEO on Wednesday, The Santa Rosa Press Democrat
reported.
</P>
<P>
   Peter L. Harris, 56, will have full day-to-day control of the
NFL franchise with an emphasis on the business end, the newspaper
said. One of his primary tasks will be reviving the stalled
stadium-shopping mall project at Candlestick Point.
</P>
<P>
   The team scheduled a 1 p.m. EDT news conference to make the
announcement.
</P>
<P>
   Harris has a reputation for turning around troubled companies,
including FAO Schwarz. The toy company hired him as CEO in 1985 and
he quadrupled profits within five years.
</P>
<P>
   Since then, Harris worked for Accolade, a San Jose video game
producer. He is now head of The Picture People, a family studio
portrait chain with 183 outlets in 19 states.
</P>
<P>
   The 49ers have not had a permanent president since Carmen Policy
left for the Cleveland Browns in 1998.
</P>
</TEXT>
