<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Actor Liam Neeson injured in motorcyle-deer accident  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   LITHGOW, N.Y. (AP) - Actor Liam Neeson suffered a broken pelvis
Tuesday when his motorcycle collided with a deer near his home,
authorities said.
</P>
<P>
   Neeson, 48, was riding his 1989 Harley Davidson motorcycle
around noon when a deer jumped out into the road, according to the
Dutchess County Sheriff's Office.
</P>
<P>
   Neeson, who wore his helmet, was thrown from the motorcycle and
landed on an earth embankment just before the motorcycle ran into a
tree in the town of Washington, about 70 miles north of New York
City.
</P>
<P>
   The Oscar-nominated Irish actor suffered a fractured right
pelvis, a chipped left pelvis, and multiple abrasions to his leg,
according to the sheriff's office.
</P>
<P>
   Herman Staats of Hyde Park was driving his truck in the area
when he spotted Neeson lying on the roadside and alerted emergency
response crews.
</P>
<P>
   ''The embankment is about 100 feet from the road and 30 feet
deep,'' Staats told the Poughkeepsie Journal. ''He managed to crawl
his way up back to the road. He wanted me to drive him back to his
house right up the road, but I could tell his hips were bothering
him.''
</P>
<P>
   Neeson was taken to a Connecticut hospital where a nursing
supervisor confirmed the actor was admitted into the emergency
room, but she refused to release any information on his condition
Tuesday night.
</P>
<P>
   ''I'm told that he's in good condition and that he's resting
comfortably,'' said Alan Nierob, Neeson's publicist. ''We're
expecting a quick recovery.''
</P>
<P>
   He was nominated for an Academy Award for his portrayal of Oskar
Schindler in the 1993 epic ''Schindler's List.'' More recently,
Neeson starred in ''Stars Wars Episode One: The Phantom Menace,''
''The Haunting,'' ''Excalibur'' and ''Rob Roy.'' Sheriff's deputies
said the deer initially ran off, but died nearby a short time after
the accident.
</P>
<P>
   Neeson married actress Natasha Richardson in 1994 at their Town
of Washington home.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
